Class List Here are the classes, structs, unions and interfaces with brief descriptions:CeLishp.Interpreter.Implementation.Constant< T >
Simple IInputValue that simply provides a constant value of type T CeLishp.Interpreter.IInputValue
Input value that can be inserted in a tree - provides a value CeLishp.Interpreter.IInterpretable
Base interface for interpretable elements CeLishp.Interpreter.INaryFunction
IInterpretable that provides a function taking one or more inputs CeLishp.Interpreter.InterpretableNode
Struct representing a node in an InterpretableTree CeLishp.Interpreter.InterpretableTree
Represents a tree of InterpretableNode CeLishp.Interpreter.InterpreterCeLishp.Parser.ISyntaxProvider
Provides syntax parsing functionality - a concrete implementation defines the syntactic layout of the language CeLishp.Interpreter.Implementation.NaryAddition
Addition function taking a variable number of inputs CeLishp.Interpreter.Implementation.NarySubtraction
Subtraction function taking two or more arguments CeLishp.Parser.Implementation.SimpleLispSyntax
One possible implementation of a ISyntaxProvider providing a simple lisp-like syntax CeLishp.Parser.SyntaxNode
A node in a syntax tree: Contains a function/keyword/literal and an optional list of child nodes CeLishp.Parser.SyntaxTree
Syntax tree representing a parsed formula CeLishp.Interpreter.Implementation.UnaryTrig
Unary trigonometry functions
